Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Business Designer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-7)

As of Business Designer Version 6.1, the function *Template comparison *is available. This function can be found in the title bar:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Select *New Comparison *to compare two templates. In the following dialog you can select the templates to be compared and, if required, the corresponding versions. The file that is already open is preselected. The files can be selected and changed by clicking on the folder icon. The *Source Template *serves as the basis and the changes are displayed from the point of view of the *Compare with *template. The order of the two files can be changed using the arrow icon in the middle of this dialog.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

If both files are selected, you can click on *Compare *to visualize the comparison. The comparison will be displayed in a new Business Designer tab and on the right-hand side, a window opens instead of the palette, in which all differences are listed.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Removed elements are shown in red, changed elements in blue and newly added elements in green. Every difference of the two templates is displayed in this list.

In the editor, the coloring of all content is reduced and only elements with differences are displayed in red, blue or green.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The differences are also shown in the outline in the colors mentioned above

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

*The classical editing of the templates is deactivated in the comparison mode In this view the differences can be visualized and depending on the rights the changes can be accepted or rejected.*

## Editing the Template Comparison
Depending on your rights, you have the possibility to edit the template comparison and thus to resolve it in order to save and further edit the newly created template. In the list of differences there are symbols for accepting (tick) and rejecting (X) a change. You can create a new template with the desired content this way. Only if all the changes have been resolved (accepted or rejected) and there are no more accept or reject symbols left, you will return to the normal editing mode and you can save the template via save button to a desired location in the Repository so you can continue editing it.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

*Currently the comparison feature does not recognize the Composer Element. This is an improvement that will be done in the future.*

> Note

*Currently the comparison fails if the freetext is set inside the template. This is a known bug that will be solved in the future.*
